**Problem 6** Suppose $f$ is twice-differentiable, $f(x) = 0$, $f'(x) = 0$, but $f''$ does
not vanish in a neighbourhood of $B$. Show 
that the error of the $k$-th Newton iteration $ε_k := x - x_k$ satisfies
$$
|ε_{k+1}| ≤ M̃ |ε_k|
$$
where 
$$
M̃ ={1 \over 2} \sup_{y \in B} |f''(y)|  \sup_{y \in B} {1 \over |f''(y)|}.
$$


**SOLUTION**

Note that
$$
f'(x_k) = f'(x) + f''(τ) ε_k = f''(τ) ε_k
$$
for some $τ$ between $x$ and $x_k$. 
Thus we get
$$
ε_{k+1}  = -{f''(t) \over 2f'(x_k)} ε_k^2 = -{f''(t) \over 2f''(τ)} ε_k.
$$
Taking absolute values of each side gives the result.


**END**
